", "closed_at": "2014-06-13T06:49:56Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "A trait impl on a reference can be used to violate lifetimes via trait objects. The following segfaults on my OSX machine:\n\n``` rust\ntrait Oops {\n    fn expose<'b>(&'b self) -> &'b Vec<u8>;\n}\n\nimpl<'a> Oops for &'a Vec<u8> {\n    fn expose<'b>(&'b self) -> &'b Vec<u8> {\n        *self\n    }\n}\n\nfn hide(x: &Vec<u8>) -> Box<Oops> {\n    box x as Box<Oops>\n}\n\nfn hidden_pointer_into_frame() -> Box<Oops> {\n    let v = vec!(37);\n    hide(&v)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let hp: Box<Oops> = hidden_pointer_into_frame();\n    let p: &Vec<u8> = hp.expose();\n    println!(\"{}\", *p)\n}\n```\n", "closed_by": {"login": "aturon", "id": 709807, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjcwOTgwNw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/709807?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon", "html_url": "https://github.com/aturon", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14868/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14868/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}